About
LEGOLAND® Dubai is the ultimate world of year-round LEGO® theme park adventures for families with children aged 2-12. It will feature over 40 interactive rides, shows and attractions and 15,000 LEGO® model structures made from over 60 million LEGO® bricks. LEGOLAND® Dubai will feature six themed lands - LEGO® CITY, ADVENTURE, KINDGOMS, IMAGINATION, FACTORY and MINILAND - each unique in their design, entertainment and playful learning experience.
Duration: More than 3 hours

    Amazingly Great as long as you are not on the short end !
    LegoLand was so fun! We had an amazing time, the rides are all kid friendly. My only issue with the entire thing is that the height limit for rides tends to be 90cm. I would advise you measure your kid in advance before going specifically for the kid in question to Motiongate and LegoLand. I would say the kids should be approximately 3 years or so to enjoy the theme park. Nontheless there are other options for the smaller ones(not as many) and fun for the kids and adults. The attention to detail is astounding! There is a mini world section. I love the theme, there is play areas for smaller ones and rides which the smaller ones can go on with parents. There are great restaurants and food stalls available. I did not stay at the hotel we stayed at Lapita which is nearby as well. We did not have many queues because we went around the 18th December but I am sure closer to Christmas would be much busier.

Mohammad Sufi Miah
Barking, UK15 contributions
Miniland and water park is where it at, rest of the park is meh
Oct 2024 • Family
It's not big, but then it's not meant to be. Most of the time the outside space in the rides area is pretty pointless due to the heat. The indoor Miniland is great.

The thing and place everyone ends up at is the Legoland Water Park. That's the place to be during the day when it's hot. Only once it cools down is it worth doing ANYTHING around this space.

The park has plenty of drink, foods and cold snack places. Also as you can imagine plenty of merchandise shops. Most of the time there is either no queue for anything at the time we went, or a queue of one other person.

Overall, for what it is, it's good, lots of water park fun, with a small smattering of the Legoland ride park itself.
Written November 3, 2024

Awesome Birthday Party Celebration at Legoland Hotel
Oct 2024 • Family
We celebrated a fantastic birthday party at the Legoland Hotel Function Room in October 2024, and it truly exceeded expectations! This vibrant, joyful space is perfect for kids and adults alike, with a lively, LEGO-themed atmosphere that creates endless fun and excitement.

Special shoutout to the amazing organizing team (Sumesh, Ritesh, Rehnuma, Fausta, Erica, Ayush, Mispa, and Lavinia), who went above and beyond to make our celebration unforgettable. Their attention to detail and dedication made the day feel extra special.

One of the best aspects is the all-inclusive package—it’s incredibly economical! Unlike many places in Dubai where you pay separately for extras like character appearances, photographers, and goody bags, everything is included here. The 2-2.5 hour event was packed with engaging activities, and afterwards, we were given access to the pool and play area, which was a wonderful bonus.

While the adult food at Bricks restaurant could be improved, the overall service and hospitality were fantastic.

Highlights of the Package:
✔ Free Valet Parking
✔ Free Goody Bags for All Kids
✔ Gift for Birthday Celebrant
✔ Character Appearance
✔ Complimentary Cake
✔ Professional Photographer
✔ Printed Photo for All Kids
✔ Creative Workshop
✔ Access to Pool and Play Area

Pro Tip: This venue is a hidden gem away from Dubai’s traffic, with a scenic, relaxing drive and plenty of greenery. The perfect first impression!

Much improvement needed to a family friendly hotel
Oct 2024 • Family
We booked for the Halloween package for our hotel stay, which includes park access, and it is a mess. We had been to the legoland in Denmark and Malaysia and this is the 3rd legoland and by far the worst in logistics although the staff were friendly and understanding. 🙁

The check in time for the resort is 3pm, and the water park closes at 5:30pm. We arrived at 12:30pm, thinking that we can first enter the water park/ theme park since it is part of the hotel package. We were directed to 4 different places, queued in all, and then in the end, was told that we need to first check in, obtain a room number before the guest service can issue us the tickets to the water/ theme parks. So after 2 hours, we finally get the tickets to get to a park that is closing after 3 hours.

The room is as the pictures and the kids love it, the treasure hunt to find the code for the safe makes the kids work for their legos in a fun manner. We then had a water drainage issue in the bathroom, where after two showers, the floor in the bathroom was flooded. 😅 we had to call help to clean/ dry the bathroom.
